How to Install pandas
Step 1: Make sure Python is installed

Check if Python is installed by running:

python --version


or

python3 --version


If not installed, download and install Python from python.org.

Step 2: (Optional) Create a virtual environment

Creating a virtual environment keeps your project dependencies separate.

# Windows
python -m venv zomato_env
zomato_env\Scripts\activate

# macOS/Linux
python3 -m venv zomato_env
source zomato_env/bin/activate

Step 3: Install pandas

Run the following command in your terminal:

pip install pandas


To install a specific version (recommended for compatibility):

pip install pandas==2.1.1

Step 4: Verify installation

Open Python or Jupyter Notebook and run:

import pandas as pd
print(pd.__version__)


If it prints the version number, pandas is installed successfully! 
